topic.title: Ingress DPU Request (IngressDpuReq)

body.p: Ingress DPU Request message supports different message length depending on total number of SGL elements.

table.title: Supported Ingress DPU Request Message Length

entry.p: * Message Length field in message header is Local Message Length plus one if it is for cascading, otherwise Message Length field is same as Local Message Length.

description.p: This field configures the ingress DPU request message type. When set to 0, this field indicates this ingress DPU request message.

field-enum-def.field-enum-desc: Ingress DPU request message. Ingress DPU request message is used as message for encryption operation only or message for full feature operation.
Ingress DPU PI request message. Ingress DPU PI request message is used as a message for PI1 and/or PI2 operation only. Not valid for this message.
Ingress DPU hash and compression request message. Ingress DPU hash and compression message is used as message for hash and/or compression operation only. Not valid for this message.
Invalid

description.p: This field configures the data flows which defines the sequences of data operations including functional bypass operations by processing engines. There are total 24 valid data flow configurations.

field-enum-def.field-enum-desc: The ingress DPU just moves the data stream from source to destination. All processing engines are bypassed
The ingress DPU performs PI operation by PI1 engine.
Invalid
The ingress DPU performs 2 cascaded PI operations by PI1 processing unit and then PI2 engine.
The ingress DPU performs hash operation by hash engine.
The ingress DPU performs PI and hash operations by PI1 engine and then hash engine.
Invalid
The ingress DPU performs 2 cascaded PI and hash operations by PI1 engine, PI2 engine, and then hash engine
The ingress DPU performs compression operation by compression engine.
The ingress DPU performs PI and compression operation by PI1 precessing unit and then compression engine.
Invalid
The ingress DPU performs 2 cascaded PI operations and compression operation by PI1 engine, PI2 engine, and then compression engine.
The ingress DPU performs data hashing and compression operations by hash engine and then compression engine.
The ingress DPU performs PI, hash and compression operations by PI1 engine, hash engine and them compression engine.
Invalid
The ingress DPU performs 2 cascaded PI, hashing and compression operations by PI1 engine, PI2 engine, hash engine and then compression engine.
The ingress DPU performs encryption operation by encryption engine. (Note this option is not applicable here but it is not necessary invalid)
The ingress DPU performances PI operation and encryption by PI1 precessing unit, and then encryption engine.
Invalid
The ingress DPU performs 2 cascaded PI operations and encryption operation by PI1 engine, PI2 engine, and then encryption engine.
The ingress DPU performs hash and encryption operations by hash engine and then encryption engine.
The ingress DPU performs PI, hash and encryption operations by PI1 engine, hash engine, and then encryption engine.
Invalid
The ingress DPU performs 2 cascaded PI operations, hash and then encryption operations by PI1 engine, PI2 engine, hash engine and then encryption engine.
The ingress DPU performs compression and encryption operations by compression engine and then encryption engine.
The ingress DPU performs PI, compression and encryption operations by PI1 precessing unit, compression engine, and then encryption engine.
Invalid
The ingress DPU performs 2 cascaded PI operations, compression and encryption operations by PI1 engine, PI2 engine, compression engine, and then encryption engine.
The ingress DPU performs hash, compression and encryption operations by hash engine, compression engine, and then encryption engine.
The ingress DPU performs PI, hash, compression and encryption operations by PI1 engine, hash engine, compression engine and them encryption engine.
Invalid
The ingress DPU performs 2 cascaded PI, hash, compression and encryption operations by PI1 engine, PI2 engine, hash engine, compression engine and then encryption engine.

description.p: For encryption only message, 0 (Bypass) and 16 (Encr) are only valid configuration.
This field set encryption operation is in blocked based operation with constant or variable block.

field-enum-def.field-enum-desc: Block based encryption operation with fixed encryption data block size. The encryption data block size is set the same as input data block size defined by EncrBlkSize field in this message.

Block based encryption operation. The encryption data block size is calculated as EncrBlkSize multiplied by embedded block number counter defined by the leading 14 bit in the first data block in each encryption data block.
Invalid

description.p: This field sets AES encryption cipher mode.

field-enum-def.field-enum-desc: The ECB mode is used for FIPS approval.
Invalid
The XTS mdoe is used for data encryption.
Invalid

description.desc-title: Encryption Data Key Tag Check Enable
description.p: This bit enables data key tag check.
If it is set to 0, the encryption data key tag is not checked. If it is set to 1, the encryption is checked before encryption operation.
This field contains data encryption key index. The data encryption key in the data encryption key table with this key index is used for the input data stream.
This field contains bytes at every block the encryption engine will skip for encryption processing.

field-enum-def.field-enum-desc: All data in each block is encrypted.
All data, except the last 4-byte, in each block is encrypted.
All data, except the last 8-byte, in each block is encrypted.
All data, except the last 16-byte, in each block is encrypted.
Invalid
All data, except the first 4-byte, in each block is encrypted.
All data, except the first 8-byte, in each block is encrypted.
All data, except the first 16-byte, in each block is encrypted.

description.p: This field specifies encryption input block size in bytes.
The encryption input block is Dword aligned. The lower 2 bits should be set always to 0.
If encryption operation mode is set to fixed block mode (EncrOpMode=0), this field is also set as encryption data block size.

If encryption operation mode is set to variable block mode (EncrOpMode =1), the encryption block size are variable, and variable block size calculated from the data block counter embedded in input data stream (leading 14-bit of the first data block in each encryption data block) . The encryption data block size = (Embedded Data Block Counter) * EncrBlkSize.
This field specifies the offset in bytes from start of the input data stream to encryption engine.
The data offset is Dword aligned. The lower 2 bits should be set always to 0.

description.desc-title: Encryption Tweak or Initial Value Bit 31:0
description.p: This field contains bit 31:0 of the Tweak value for XTS cipher mode. The field is ignored for ECB cipher mode

description.desc-title: Encryption Tweak or Initial Value Bit 63:32
description.p: This field contains bit 63:32 of the Tweak value for XTS cipher mode. The field is ignored for ECB cipher mode

description.desc-title: Encryption Tweak or Initial Value Bit 95:64
description.p: This field contains bit 95:64 of Tweak value for XTS cipher mode. The field is ignored for ECB cipher mode.

description.desc-title: Encryption Tweak or Initial Value Bit 127:96
description.p: This field contains bit 127:96 of Tweak value for XTS cipher mode. The field is ignored for ECB cipher mode.
This field contains lower 32-bit (31:0) of data encryption key tag used for key tag check. If the data encryption key check is disabled this field is ignored.
This field contains up 32-bit (63:32) of data encryption key tag used for key tag check. If the data encryption key check is disabled this field is ignored.
This field contains the lower 32-bits of the 40-bit starting address of source memory region 0.

description.p: If the ingressDPU only contain PI operations (DataFlowCfg = 0 or 1) , this value should be always set to 0.
This field is ignored if both PI1 and PI2 are disabled.
This field controls whether an interrupt is generated when a PI operation completes (either PI1 or PI2)

field-enum-def.field-enum-desc: An interrupt is generated when PI operation completes (PI1 or PI2)
No interrupt is generated when PI (PI1 or PI2) operation completes.

description.p: This field is ignored if both PI1 and PI2 are disabled, or the PI completion messaging is disabled (PICplMsgEn = 0)

description.desc-title: Outbound Message Queue for PI Completion
description.p: This field selects the outbound message queue number on which the outbound message (completion message) resulting from PI completion (either PI1 or PI2) is enqueued. This queue ID can be the same as OutMsgQueue if both completion uses the same queue.
This field is ignored if both PI1 and PI2 are disabled, or the PI completion messaging is disabled (PICplMsgEn = 0)
This field set hash operation mode as block based operation or stream based operation

field-enum-def.field-enum-desc: Block based hash operation. Each block from the input data stream is hashed with the default initial digest.
Stream based hash operation starting with a new data stream, it is not the last data stream for the hash session.
Stream based hash operation with continuing previous hash session, it is not the last data stream for the hash session
Stream based hash operation with continuing previous hash session, it is the last data stream for the hash session.
Stream based hash operation starting with a new data stream and it is the last data stream for the hash session as well.
Invalid

description.p: This bit select hashing algorithm of SHA3-256 or SHA3-512.

field-enum-def.field-enum-desc: Hash algorithm is SHA3-256
Hash algorithm is SHA3-512

description.p: This bit defines hash digest 0 offset in completion message when there is only one SHA256 digest in the completion message.

field-enum-def.field-enum-desc: Hash digest 0 is starting at Dword 8. This value is set if 1) there is one and only one hash SHA3-256 digest with as result of the hash operation, and 2) There is maximum one meta data as the result of compression operation.
Hash digest 0 is starting at Dword 16.

description.p: This bit is valid only when hash operation is enabled, otherwise it is ignored.

description.desc-title: Byte Length for Last Input Data Dword
description.p: This field contains the length of valid bytes in the last input Dword for hash operation.

field-enum-def.field-enum-desc: All 4 bytes (Bit 31:0) is valid. Default for normal Dword aligned operation.
Byte 0 (Bit 7:0) is valid , Byte 3:1 (Bit 31:8) is not valid.
Byte 1:0 (Bit 15:0) are valid, Byte 3:2 (Bit 31:16) are not valid.
Byte 2:0 (Bit 23:0) are valid, Byte 3 (Bit 31:24) is not valid.

description.p: This field contains the number of bytes at the end of every block the hash engine will skip for hash processing. If the value is 0, no byte will be skipped.
The hash skip number is Dword aligned, the lower 2-bit of this field should be set to 0.
This field is valid only for Block Based Hash operation mode. It is ignored when Stream Based Hash operation mode is enabled.
This field contains block size in bytes for hash engine. The block size is defined for the input data stream of hash engine.
The hash block size is Dword aligned, the lower 2-bit of this field should be set to 0.
This field is valid only for Block Based Hash operation mode. It is ignored when Stream Based Hash operation mode is enabled.
This field specifies the offset in bytes from start of the input data stream to hash engine.
This field contains uncompressed data block size in bytes for compression engine. The uncompressed data block size is defined as data block size before compression.
The logic block is Dword aligned. The lower 2 bits should be set always to 0.
This field specifies the offset in bytes from start of the input data stream for compression engine.
The data offset is Dword aligned. The lower 2 bits should be set always to 0.
This field contains compressed data block size in bytes for compression engine. The compressed data block size is defined as data block size after compression.
The logic block is Dword aligned. The lower 2 bits should be set always to 0.
This field set hash operation mode as block based operation.

field-enum-def.field-enum-desc: Block based compression operation. Each block from the input data stream is compressed with history buffer reset before compression. The compressed data for each block ,will be packed into one or more compressed data blocks.
Invalid

description.p: This bit configures whether compression 4-byte statistic meta data per uncompressed block is generated and inserted to compressed data for each uncompressed data block or entire uncompressed data stream.

If it is set to 0, no compression meta is attached. If it is set to 1, the 4-byte compression meta data is generated and inserted at the beginning of the first compressed data block for each uncompressed data block in block based compression mode.
The 4-byte compression meta data for block based compression includes 2-byte compressed data block counter with packing information and 2-byte compressed data length.
This bit configures whether compression 4-byte CRC per uncompressed block is generated and inserted to compressed data for each uncompressed data block or entire uncompressed data stream.

If it is set to 0, no CRC is attached. If it is set to 1, the 4-byte CRC (Adler32 checksum) is generated and inserted at the end of the compressed data for each uncompressed data block in block based compression mode.

This bit configures whether the compressed data integrity is checked. If it is set to '0', no data integrity check for compressed data. If it is set to '1', the data integrity check is performed by decompressing the compressed data with embedded decompress logic inside the ingress DPU, and checking the Adler32 checksum.
This bit is ignored and no data integrity check will be performed for the compressed data if Adler32 checksum is not enabled (CompCRCIns=0)
This bit configures whether the compression unit will output original data before compression or compressed data after compression if the data block is incompressible.
If it is set to 0, the compression unit will output the compressed data (which means its size is larger than uncompressed data). If it is set to 1, the compression unit will output the original data.
